  "datePublished": "2026-03-20",
  "description": "A Refocusing is a morphism (H, t*) → (H', t') between MacroFoci — a pair (ρ, φ) of a presheaf transition ρ and a history reassignment φ that moves the designated focal history from t* to t'. Three structurally distinct cases: forward extension (t' = s★t*, H' = G_s(H)), backward restriction (t' \u003c t*, H' = H), and lateral shift (t' incomparable with t*, H' = H). In every case the new MacroFocus (H', t') is fully constituted by the refocusing; the Gurwitsch tripartition reconstitutes around t'. Formally a morphism in the category of pointed presheaves.",
  "name": "Refocusing",
